    <chapter id="key-points">
        <title>
            <control>Key Points:</control>
        </title>
        <tip>
            <list>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <control>Heap Memory</control>
                        : Reference types are stored in heap memory, and variables hold a reference to the memory
                        location.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <control>Shared Data</control>
                        : Assigning one reference type variable to another makes them both reference the same object in
                        memory.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <control>Object Types</control>
                        : Classes, interfaces, and arrays are examples of reference types in C#.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <control>Mutability</control>
                        : Reference types allow the data they point to be modified, and changes are reflected across all
                        references to that object.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </list>
        </tip>
